         <abstract id="aspace_5513f9af1c6c5fe96faaf07e7b92b2ad">The collection consists of seven letters written by William Morris to friends and acquaintances, and a group of autograph manuscripts by Morris. One manuscript, "The Wood Beyond the World," is accompanied by a drawing made for the book by Sir Edward Coley Burne-Jones, and two impressions of the resulting engraving. Also present is a letter to the American collector Dean Sage regarding one of the manuscripts.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n78095326" source="naf">
               <part>Morris, William, 1834-1896</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
