               <odd id="aspace_5ef3585881ce05afb0b2100935f815cc">
                  <head>General note</head>
                  <p>Four lectures delivered in Birmingham, London, and Nottingham: "The Art of the People" (23 p.); The Beauty of Life" (31 p.); Making the Best of It" (35 p.); The Prospects of Architecture in Civilization" (38 p.).</p>
                  <p>Also bound in: "Westminster Abbey"; autograph manuscript (12 p.) accompanied by printed pamphlet <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>Concerning Westminster Abbey</part>
                     </title> (London: Society for the Protection of Ancient Buildings, 1893)</p>
                  <p>Also bound in: "Arts and Crafts"; autograph manuscript, signed (4 p.), preface to <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>Arts and Crafts Essays by Members of the Arts and Crafts Exhibition Society</part>
                     </title> (London: Rivington, Percival &amp; Co., 1893).</p>
               </odd>
